00:30:37.020 --> 00:30:39.080
Catch it, here I go back
door, here's a drop.

00:30:39.080 --> 00:30:40.430
Off I go.

00:30:40.430 --> 00:30:42.173
So, it's playing those
sequences and understanding

00:30:42.173 --> 00:30:43.540
what the defense is gonna do again,

00:30:43.540 --> 00:30:44.373
so I made them dangerous.

00:30:44.373 --> 00:30:46.030
That's why Chicago was so dangerous,

00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:49.410
'cause they knew how Utah was on' play.

00:30:49.410 --> 00:30:51.940
These actions, and then
they all five of them

00:30:51.940 --> 00:30:52.902
took advantage of it.

00:30:52.902 --> 00:30:54.380
- And they always keep you with space.

00:30:54.380 --> 00:30:55.213
- Always.

00:30:55.213 --> 00:30:57.170
- All the time, you'll
never lap over each other.

00:30:57.170 --> 00:30:58.003
- No, always.

00:30:58.003 --> 00:31:00.810
They were really big on
having 10 to 15 foot spacing.

00:31:00.810 --> 00:31:01.643
Always.

00:31:01.643 --> 00:31:03.470
- So, this is what I wanna know, right.

00:31:04.670 --> 00:31:07.740
When I came, well, couple
say coming into the league,

00:31:07.740 --> 00:31:09.985
I feel like I was offense on score, right?

00:31:09.985 --> 00:31:12.540
You know, you in high school,
come out with a score.

00:31:12.540 --> 00:31:14.190
But then you look at dudes like you.

00:31:14.190 --> 00:31:15.910
I wanna know what is the mentality

00:31:15.910 --> 00:31:18.660
when you gat, all right
you got 20, you got 30.

00:31:18.660 --> 00:31:21.010
What makes in your mind when you get 30,

00:31:21.010 --> 00:31:23.470
most people, like, all right, cool.?

00:31:23.470 --> 00:31:24.740
I'm going 40.

00:31:24.740 --> 00:31:25.620
I'm going 50.

00:31:25.620 --> 00:31:26.770
Now, I'm going 60.

00:31:26.770 --> 00:31:29.280
Now, I'm going, like, what is happening

00:31:29.280 --> 00:31:33.060
in your though process,
intuitive, life if, at some point,

00:31:33.060 --> 00:31:36.180
I know you're tired, 'cause
people don't understand.

00:31:36.180 --> 00:31:39.310
Score (mumbles) is like
that, that take energy.

00:31:39.310 --> 00:31:42.120
So, how do you continue to just go,

00:31:42.120 --> 00:31:45.450
because I was in New
York when you got the 60.

00:31:45.450 --> 00:31:50.110
And God bless my young
boy, Wilson Chandler.

00:31:50.110 --> 00:31:51.785
He recovered, he is good.

00:31:51.785 --> 00:31:53.467
Everything is good with
his life, his career,

00:31:53.467 --> 00:31:55.610
his still playing now, so you know,

00:31:55.610 --> 00:31:58.920
he made it through that but
I'm sitting here watching

00:31:58.920 --> 00:32:02.270
