I didn't teach her that.

00:35:25.633 --> 00:35:26.827
- She got the face.

00:35:26.827 --> 00:35:28.380
(mumbling)

00:35:28.380 --> 00:35:30.190
She got the face, everything.

00:35:30.190 --> 00:35:31.023
- She's aggressive.

00:35:31.023 --> 00:35:34.600
You know, it's not something
that we taught her how to be.

00:35:34.600 --> 00:35:36.200
She's just naturally aggressive.

00:35:37.154 --> 00:35:37.987
- Got it.
- Yeah so,

00:35:37.987 --> 00:35:39.550
- You just (mumbles)

00:35:39.550 --> 00:35:41.390
- Always kind of aggressive
and temperamental

00:35:41.390 --> 00:35:43.400
and I grew up in a competitive household.

00:35:43.400 --> 00:35:45.342
My cousins were all competitive

00:35:45.342 --> 00:35:47.450
and we compete at everything,
trash talk everything.

00:35:47.450 --> 00:35:50.963
So, that kind of added to the
feistiness of it a little bit.

00:35:51.950 --> 00:35:53.860
- We fell in love with this ball.

00:35:53.860 --> 00:35:55.587
This ball then showed us the world,

00:35:55.587 --> 00:35:58.620
and it showed us so many different things.

00:35:58.620 --> 00:36:01.860
To see your daughter fall in love

00:36:01.860 --> 00:36:04.665
with the same ball that
you fell in love with,

00:36:04.665 --> 00:36:06.770
how did it, how that makes you feel?

00:36:06.770 --> 00:36:08.760
And to coach her
- with that passion.

00:36:08.760 --> 00:36:10.770
- To help her out, to
give her the juice of it,

00:36:10.770 --> 00:36:13.365
like have a passion for
it, like, care about it.

00:36:13.365 --> 00:36:16.090
- It's a great feeling but,
it would've been the same

00:36:16.090 --> 00:36:17.670
if it was anything else,

00:36:17.670 --> 00:36:19.130
as long as they got the passion for it.

00:36:19.130 --> 00:36:20.670
That's the hardest thing is trying to find

00:36:20.670 --> 00:36:22.410
something that your kids
are passionate about.

00:36:22.410 --> 00:36:24.340
My eldest loves film.

00:36:24.340 --> 00:36:26.700
She loves volleyball too,
but really loves film.

00:36:26.700 --> 00:36:28.750
And Gianna loves basketball.

00:36:28.750 --> 00:36:31.260
All right, cool, I know
basketball, I can teach you.

00:36:31.260 --> 00:36:34.580
So, it's also because
it's like a blank canvas

00:36:34.580 --> 00:36:36.220
when I first started two years ago.

00:36:36.220 --> 00:36:38.650
So, I started teaching
them all the footwork.

00:36:38.650 --> 00:36:40.860
It took me 20 years to learn.

00:36:40.860 --> 00:36:43.070
I'm teaching them now at 11.

00:36:43.070 --> 00:36:45.370
So now at 13, they fade away.

00:36:45.370 --> 00:36:47.680
There are up and unders, their spin moves,

00:36:47.680 --> 00:36:49.100
their balance, like their footwork

00:36:49.100 --> 00:36:52.370
is really really sharp because
it's like a blank canvas.

00:36:52.370 --> 00:36:56.040
And it's fun to watch them figure it out.

00:36:56.040 --> 00:36:57.587
You know, to watch them learn and like

00:36:57.587 --> 00:36:59.710
- Did you ever think you would coach?

00:36:59.710 --> 00:37:02.120
- No, I didn't think my kids
would ever play basketball.

00:37:02.120 --> 00:37:04.460
- Yeah, I was thinking like, I wish

00:37:04.460 --> 00:37:05.620
my kids can do anything.

00:37:05.620 --> 00:37:07.730
Anything you wanna do, I gonna support it.

00:37:07.730 --> 00:37:10.910
But when you choose the one
thing that I fell in love with,

00:37:10.910 --> 00:37:13.750
it's like, it's still
a special thing to me,

00:37:13.750 --> 00:37:15.120
like, babies, you love this?

00:37:15.120 --> 00:37:16.170
- No, it's exciting.
- I'll give you

00:37:16.170 --> 00:37:18.018
everything you need.

00:37:18.018 --> 00:37:19.130
- It's exciting and you
get a chance to go back

00:37:19.130 --> 00:37:21.380
and go through the basics all over again.

00:37:21.380 --> 00:37:24.100
So, I have practice plans everyday.

00:37:24.100 --> 00:37:27.000
And it's like a six year
plan and we're in year two

00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:29.720
right now, so you can patiently teach them

00:37:29.720 --> 00:37:30.980
every little aspect.

00:37:30.980 --> 00:37:33.650
Teach them how to use screens,
teach them how to be patient,

00:37:33.650 --> 00:37:36.010
teach them how to anticipate on defense.

00:37:36.010 --> 00:37:38.360
All those little balance,
all that little stuff.

00:37:38.360 --> 00:37:40.470
It's awesome, man, it's awesome.

00:37:40.470 --> 00:37:43.130
- So, I want you to take a
second to talk to me about

00:37:43.130 --> 00:37:44.683
The Legacy and The Queen.

00:37:45.700 --> 00:37:47.290
And how this came about.

00:37:47.290 --> 00:37:49.518
I like the (mumbling)

00:37:49.518 --> 00:37:52.370
the tennis, the tennis
ball feel with like,

00:37:52.370 --> 00:37:54.620
this is, this is not just something.

00:37:54.620 --> 00:37:56.830
To me, this is something, as a kid,

00:37:56.830 --> 00:37:58.870
you get excited about the color and like,

00:37:58.870 --> 00:38:00.590
this is like when I would buy CDs.

00:38:00.590 --> 00:38:01.890
You know, we buying Nolan.

00:38:01.890 --> 00:38:04.040
It was like, look at the graphics.

00:38:04.040 --> 00:38:06.460
This is like in comparison, 'cause this is

00:38:06.460 --> 00:38:07.660
not your normal book.

00:38:07.660 --> 00:38:10.000
You got feel and texture and sparkles

00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:12.220
and then it still got the tennis racket.

00:38:12.220 --> 00:38:14.400
So, talk about how you
cam up with this thing.

00:38:14.400 --> 00:38:16.410
- Well, we wanted to create something

00:38:17.570 --> 00:38:22.313
for children that they feel
that they're important.

00:38:23.420 --> 00:38:24.850
Like a lot of time, in
the children's space,

00:38:24.850 --> 00:38:27.060
we kind of dumb stuff
down, the materials down

00:38:27.060 --> 00:38:28.065
because it's for children.

00:38:28.065 --> 00:38:29.770
They're not gonna tell the difference.

00:38:29.770 --> 00:38:32.120
But I feel like if we create
something that's high in value,

00:38:32.120 --> 00:38:33.770
they understand it as being cared for.

00:38:33.770 --> 00:38:36.500
That means that they matter and they do.

00:38:36.500 --> 00:38:38.230
For parents as well, you
look at this and you put this

00:38:38.230 --> 00:38:40.720
book up and you can feel that
there's been a lot of care

00:38:40.720 --> 00:38:41.553
put into it.

00:38:41.553 --> 00:38:43.220
You may not understand all the hidden gems

00:38:43.220 --> 00:38:44.600
that are in this book yet.

00:38:44.600 --> 00:38:45.600
But you can feel them.

00:38:45.600 --> 00:38:48.450
So you understand, this is
a studio that we can trust.

00:38:48.450 --> 00:38:49.840
And then for the story itself,

00:38:49.840 --> 00:38:52.540
it's about how do we
teach kids how to handle

00:38:52.540 --> 00:38:54.420
the inner monologue?

00:38:54.420 --> 00:38:56.490
The emotional things that we experience,

00:38:56.490 --> 00:38:57.470
how do we teach them that?

00:38:57.470 --> 00:38:59.330
Which is why it had to be tennis.

00:38:59.330 --> 00:39:01.330
Because tennis is such
an individual sport.

00:39:01.330 --> 00:39:02.163
- And it's hard.

00:39:02.163 --> 00:39:03.200
- But different that golf.

00:39:03.200 --> 00:39:06.156
Golf, you're dealing with
the elements and yourself.

00:39:06.156 --> 00:39:07.960
And tennis, you're dealing with yourself,

00:39:07.960 --> 00:39:10.240
the elements and that
person across the net

00:39:10.240 --> 00:39:12.040
from you trying to beat you, right.

00:39:12.040 --> 00:39:13.900
So you gotta have those
inner conversations,

00:39:13.900 --> 00:39:15.650
navigate those while competing

00:39:15.650 --> 00:39:19.408
with somebody else who's
across the net from you.

00:39:19.408 --> 00:39:21.850
- The story behind it, what inspired you

00:39:21.850 --> 00:39:23.690
to do that story?

00:39:23.690 --> 00:39:27.690
- Well, the way I look at it,
inspiration drives the world.

00:39:27.690 --> 00:39:30.050
So, if I'm looking at the
kingdoms in the worlds

00:39:30.050 --> 00:39:33.430
that we create,
inspiration is what decides

00:39:33.430 --> 00:39:34.900
who's going to be the ruler

00:39:34.900 --> 00:39:36.690
of these particular worlds?

00:39:36.690 --> 00:39:37.880
All right, so them how you inspire?

